MoldingInfo.Description: Thin films with various TiO2 loadings (0.5, 1.0, 3.0 and 5.0 wt% final nanoparticle concentration) were prepared by casting the corresponding solution onto a glass Petri dish to evaporate the chloroform at room temperature; no freestanding film formation was observed.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Experiments were carried out in the tensile mode on rectangular shaped bars, in the temperature range between 120 and 300 C at a heating rate of 2 C min1 and frequencies of 0.1, 1 and 10 Hz.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: A Perkin-Elmer Spectrum One spectrometer equipped with a Universal ATR sampling accessory (a diamond crystal) and a red laser excitation source (632.8 nm) was used to obtain the room temperature attenuated total reectance FT-IR spectra.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: X-ray diffraction (XRD) measurements were performed with a Bruker D8 Advance diffractometer using a Cu tube as an X-ray source (l CuKa 1⁄4 1.54 A ̊), with a voltage of 40 kV and an intensity of 40 mA.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: Prior to the measurements, samples were dried overnight at 100 C. The temperature was scanned from 25 to 900 C under both nitrogen and dry air atmospheres at a heating rate of 10 C min1.
